    "Identification of a lead combination of drugs based on the top approved drugsBased on the 15 drug candidates identified, drug combinations, ranging from two-drug to six-drug combinations, have been generated by DeepDrug (see \"Drug Combination Optimisation\").",
    "Figure 2 shows the distribution of the drug combination scores from two-drug combinations up to six-drug combinations.The top ten five-drug combinations for AD among 3,003 combinations (choosing 5 from 15 drugs) are shown in Table 2.",
    "The small variations in the top five-drug combination scores align with previous experimental and simulation results, which suggest that an effective high-order drug combination is not \"a needle in a haystack\"DeepDrug Ranking DeepDrug Score Drug Approved Treatment Description 0.2692 Tofacitinib Rheumatic conditions Janus kinase (JAK) inhibitor 0.1528 Niraparib Cancer Poly-ADP ribose polymerase (PARP) inhibitor 0.1454 Palbociclib Cancer Cyclin-dependent kinase 4/6 (CDK4/6) inhibitor 0.1446 Filgotinib Rheumatic conditions JAK inhibitor 0.1436 Baricitinib Rheumatic conditions JAK inhibitor 0.1318 Sirolimus Organ transplant rejection Mammalian target of rapamycin (mTOR) inhibitor 0.1195 Empagliflozin Diabetes Sodium-glucose co-transporter-2 (SGLT2) inhibitor 0.1096 Febuxostat Hyperuricemia Gout Xanthine oxidase (XO) inhibitor 0.1084 Raloxifene Osteoporosis Estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) 0.0964 Doxercalciferol Hyperparathyroidism Vitamin D2 analog 0.0939 Valproic Acid Seizures Fatty acid derivative and anticonvulsant 0.0938 Miconazole Fungal infections Azole antifungal 0.0937 Zinc Acetate Zinc deficiency Wilson's disease Zinc 0.0936 Adenosine Supraventricular tachycardia Antiarrhythmic agent 0.0917 Olanzapine Schizophrenia Bipolar I disorder Antipsychotic agent Table 1.",
